    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of the cross section of an electrically neutral metal sphere. The sphere has a radius of R, and 3 points are indicated on the sphere. Point 1 is located on the left side of the sphere. A particle of charge positive Q is located at a distance of R over 2 to the left of point 1. Point 2 is located at the top of the sphere, and point 3 is located on the right side of the sphere.\" src=\"/images/485063f9238d96f4432594b77aee9b47.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The cross section of an electrically neutral metal sphere of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>R</mi></math></span></span> is shown in the figure. A small particle with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive Q\"><math alttext=\"positive Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> is located a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction R over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction R over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span> from the surface of the sphere. Which of the following correctly ranks the electrostatic potentials <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 1\"><math alttext=\"V sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 2\"><math alttext=\"V sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"V sub 3\"><math alttext=\"V sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></span></span> on the sphereâ€™s surface at points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, respectively?</p>\n",
